{"/service/ndnp/vnstcsc/batch_vnstcsc_ensomned_ver01/data/sn84037503/00513689810/1958041601/0615.xml":{"full_text":"Speech of Atty, John Maduro\nOver Radio Station WSTA\nof these states to take care of the\nunemployed have been exhausted\nbecause of the great demands on\nthem and in some instances the\nFederal Government has had to\nmake substantial contribution to\nthe State funds,\nHere in the Virgin Islands w e\nhave 1 few programs designed t 2\nas..st the aged, blind, children\nand handicapped persons, but there\nis no program in these Islands whic\nwill render assistance to a man who\nhas been laid off of his job for one\nreason or other, except ifhe is a\nFederal employee for Federal\nemployees are covered under the\nFederal Employee Insurance P ro\ngram, We need legislation which\nwill establish such a program thru\nwhich our unemployed will re\nceive some assistance whenever\nthe occasfon warrants it,\nThere is no doubt in our mi nds\nthat should this recession in the\nUnited States continue, we here\nin the Virgin Islands would be\naffected, When we compare the\nplacement figures of em p 10 yees\nWwho obtained jobs through the\nEmployment Office here we found\nthat the number of placements bet\nween the months of January to\nMarch, 1958 were much less than\nthey were for the same period inl\n1957, Os course there is no reaso n\nfor alarm, however, we still feel\nthat now is the time to give so me:\nserious thoughtto this ent r e\nmatter rather than waiting u n til\nthe recession is on our backs,\nThe Unity Party is since re Iy,\ninterested in the economic growth\nand development of the Virgin Is=\nlands, and we feel that in order to\nproperly take care of the respons i='\nbilities which come with se If\ngovermnment, we muststart now\ndevising ways and means of bo Is\ntering our economy,\nMy friends, before closing, I\nwish to share this observation with\nyou, From the reports made by\nAnduze and Lawaetz on their re\ncent trip to \"7ashington, one gets\nthe impression thatour rec ent\nMarch on Government House so\nannoyed the members of Congress\nthat our chances of getting a Resi\n\u201cdent Commissioner in Washing t on\nand obtaining greater autonomy\nfor the people in the Virgin Is-\nlands are retarded, i\nMy friends, we do not believe\nthat this is the case, The C on-\ngressional records indicate that at\nthe time the present Organic Act\nwas under consideration, mem-=-\nbers of Congress expressed them=|\nselves on the matter of a Virg in\nIslands Resident Commissioner to\nthe effect that because of the\nsmall population in the V irgin\nIslands there is no justifica t ion\nfor an additional expenditure of\nthousands of dollars of Federal\nfunds to maintain such an office\nin Washington, In addition, just\na few weeks ago in a letter to\nMr, Hill, Senator Murray ex\npressed the same opinion and we\nfeel therefore, that the March on\nGovernment House would h ave\nabsolutely nothing to do with the\ndelay of a passage of Congress of\na Bill for a Residence Commiss\nioner from the Virgin Isl ands,\nWe also feel that the Membe r s\nof Congress, responsible rep r e\nsentatives of the people wh o\ncomprise one of the greatest\ndemocracies in the world, would\nnever penalize other America n\ncitizens for exercising a basic|\ndemocratic right given the ml\nunder the First Amendment of the\nUnited States Constitution, That\nright being the right of the people\ntc peaceable assemble and peti\ntion the Government forth e\u2019\nredress of grfe vonces,\nThank you for listening ladies l\nand gentlemen and 2ood night!\nBell 1\nVM y\nLARI\nGrundig\nGeorge\u2019s E\nTHE HOME JOURNAL\nNOTI CE\nIn accordance with Section 9(d)of Act\nNo. 224( Bill N0.479)0f t he Se cond Legisla\nture of the Virgin Islands, To Encourag\u00e9g\nthe Establishment of New Business and\nIndustries- -to Attr act I nvest ment Capital\nin Order to furt her the Economic Dec vel op\nment of the I slands--to promote Tourism\nand the Building of Additional Hotels and\nGue st Houses and Housing Projects-throwgh.\nthe Granting of Spec: al Subsidi es and for\n~other Purposes\u2019'\u2019, sarcti oned and approved\non-the sth day of July 1957, and Rule s\nand Regulations of the Virginls lands,\nBoard of Tax Ex\u00e9mption, a .PUB L I.\u00b0'C\nHEARING on the following appli cants seek\ning exemptions and subsidi es will be held\non Thursday, May 1,1958 at 8:00 p.m, at\nthe Municipal Court Building, Charlotte\nAmalie, St, Thomas, Virgin Islands:\nNAME OF APPLI CANT ADDRESS TWPE\nBUSINESS\nV.l.Jewelry Manufac- Estate Jewelry\nturing Corporation Thomas, Factory\nSt. Thomas L s\nV.I. s\nVirgin I sle Hotel,lnc, Estate Resort\nLower Hotel\nJohn\nDunkoe,\n.St. Thomas\nWest Indian Products Bourne Fd, Manuface\nLtd, St T homas, t ure of:\n\u2018drugs\nres chemic~\nal s, bot\ntling;\nwinebase\nproducts\nY vodka\ndrinks o\nalcohol ic\nnahure not\npresent ly\nm anus ac\ntured on\nisland.\nAny person,firm or corporation interest\ned in the approval or di sappr oval of an ap\nplication, may appear and be heard provide d\na written statement is submitted to the Board\nat 1 east one week prior to the Hearing B\nsuch application,\nJames A. O\u2019 Br yan\nExecutive Secretary\nfpril 11,1958","height":"14424","width":"11292"}}
